Note:
RUNA Traceback Library: Security Vulnerability Scanner

Advanced security analysis system for detecting vulnerabilities in stack traces,
identifying security-sensitive code paths, and providing comprehensive security
assessments with remediation guidance. Uses rule-based analysis and pattern matching.

Key Features:
- SQL injection detection in stack traces and error messages
- Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability identification
- Path traversal and directory traversal detection
- Authentication and authorization bypass indicators
- Cryptographic weakness identification in error contexts
- Information disclosure through stack traces
- Input validation failure detection
- Privilege escalation pattern recognition
- Buffer overflow and memory corruption indicators
- Security configuration error detection
:End Note

Import module "traceback/traceback" as TracebackCore
Import module "traceback/patterns" as PatternAnalysis
Import module "collections" as Collections
Import module "string/string" as StringUtils

Note: Security Vulnerability Types and Configuration
Type called "SecurityVulnerability":
            vulnerability_id as String
            vulnerability_type as VulnerabilityType
            severity_level as SecuritySeverity
            title as String
            description as String
            affected_components as List[String]
            attack_vectors as List[AttackVector]
            cve_references as List[String]
            remediation_steps as List[RemediationStep]
            confidence_score as Float
            risk_score as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type VulnerabilityType is:
            | SQLInjection
            | CrossSiteScripting
            | PathTraversal
            | AuthenticationBypass
            | AuthorizationBypass
            | CryptographicWeakness
            | InformationDisclosure
            | InputValidationFailure
            | PrivilegeEscalation
            | BufferOverflow
            | CommandInjection
            | DeserializationVulnerability
            | ConfigurationError
            | WeakRandomness
            | InsecureTransmission

Type SecuritySeverity is:
            | Critical
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | Informational

Type called "AttackVector":
            vector_type as AttackVectorType
            description as String
            prerequisites as List[String]
            impact_level as ImpactLevel
            exploitability as ExploitabilityLevel
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type AttackVectorType is:
            | RemoteCodeExecution
            | DataExfiltration
            | PrivilegeEscalation
            | DenialOfService
            | DataManipulation
            | SystemCompromise
            | InformationGathering

Type ImpactLevel is:
            | None
            | Low
            | Medium
            | High
            | Complete

Type ExploitabilityLevel is:
            | Theoretical
            | Difficult
            | Moderate
            | Easy
            | Trivial

Type called "RemediationStep":
            step_id as String
            category as RemediationCategory
            description as String
            code_example as Optional[String]
            priority as Priority
            estimated_effort as EstimatedEffort
            dependencies as List[String]
            verification_method as String
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RemediationCategory is:
            | InputValidation
            | OutputEncoding
            | AccessControl
            | CryptographicFix
            | ConfigurationChange
            | CodeRefactoring
            | LibraryUpdate
            | SecurityTesting

Type Priority is:
            | Immediate
            | High
            | Medium
            | Low
            | Deferred

Type EstimatedEffort is:
            | Minutes
            | Hours
            | Days
            | Weeks
            | Months

Type called "SecurityScanResult":
            scan_id as String
            scan_timestamp as Integer
            scanned_exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo
            vulnerabilities_found as List[SecurityVulnerability]
            security_score as Float
            risk_assessment as RiskAssessment
            compliance_violations as List[ComplianceViolation]
            recommendations as List[SecurityRecommendation]
            false_positive_likelihood as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "RiskAssessment":
            overall_risk_level as RiskLevel
            confidentiality_impact as ImpactLevel
            integrity_impact as ImpactLevel
            availability_impact as ImpactLevel
            business_risk_factors as List[String]
            technical_risk_factors as List[String]
            mitigation_urgency as UrgencyLevel
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RiskLevel is:
            | VeryLow
            | Low
            | Medium
            | High
            | VeryHigh
            | Critical

Type UrgencyLevel is:
            | Emergency
            | Urgent
            | Standard
            | LowPriority
            | Deferred

Type called "ComplianceViolation":
            standard_name as String
            violation_id as String
            requirement_reference as String
            description as String
            compliance_severity as ComplianceSeverity
            remediation_guidance as String
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ComplianceSeverity is:
            | MustFix
            | ShouldFix
            | CouldFix
            | Informational

Type called "SecurityRecommendation":
            recommendation_id as String
            category as SecurityCategory
            title as String
            description as String
            implementation_guidance as String
            cost_benefit_analysis as CostBenefitAnalysis
            priority_score as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type SecurityCategory is:
            | PreventiveControl
            | DetectiveControl
            | CorrectiveControl
            | SecurityEducation
            | ProcessImprovement
            | TechnologyUpgrade

Type called "CostBenefitAnalysis":
            implementation_cost as ImplementationCost
            risk_reduction_benefit as Float
            operational_impact as OperationalImpact
            payback_period as PaybackPeriod
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ImplementationCost is:
            | Minimal
            | Low
            | Moderate
            | High
            | VeryHigh

Type OperationalImpact is:
            | NoImpact
            | MinimalImpact
            | ModerateImpact
            | HighImpact
            | SignificantImpact

Type PaybackPeriod is:
            | Immediate
            | ShortTerm
            | MediumTerm
            | LongTerm
            | Uncertain

Note: Security Vulnerability Detection Engine
Process called "scan_for_security_vulnerabilities" that takes exception_info as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns SecurityScanResult:
    Note: Comprehensive security vulnerability scan
            Let scan_id be generate_scan_id
    Let scan_timestamp be TracebackCore.get_current_timestamp Let vulnerabilities be list containing Note: Scan for different vulnerability types
            Let sql_injection_vulns be detect_sql_injection with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in sql_injection_vulns:
            Add to vulnerabilities vuln Let xss_vulns be detect_cross_site_scripting with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in xss_vulns:
            Add to vulnerabilities vuln Let path_traversal_vulns be detect_path_traversal with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in path_traversal_vulns:
            Add to vulnerabilities vuln Let auth_vulns be detect_authentication_issues with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in auth_vulns:
            Add to vulnerabilities vuln Let crypto_vulns be detect_cryptographic_weaknesses with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in crypto_vulns:
            Add to vulnerabilities vuln Let info_disclosure_vulns be detect_information_disclosure with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in info_disclosure_vulns:
            Add to vulnerabilities vuln Let input_validation_vulns be detect_input_validation_failures with exception as exception_info
    For each vuln in input_validation_vulns:
    Add to vulnerabilities vuln Note: Calculate security score and risk assessment
            Let security_score be calculate_security_score with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities
    Let risk_assessment be assess_security_risk with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities and exception as exception_info Note: Check compliance violations
    Let compliance_violations be check_compliance_violations with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities Note: Generate security recommendations
    Let recommendations be generate_security_recommendations with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities Note: Calculate false positive likelihood
    Let false_positive_likelihood be calculate_false_positive_likelihood with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities Return SecurityScanResult with:
            scan_id as scan_id
            scan_timestamp as scan_timestamp
            scanned_exception as exception_info
            vulnerabilities_found as vulnerabilities
            security_score as security_score
            risk_assessment as risk_assessment
            compliance_violations as compliance_violations
            recommendations as recommendations
            false_positive_likelihood as false_positive_likelihood
            metadata as dictionary containing "scan_duration_ns" as calculate_scan_duration, "vulnerability_count" as length of vulnerabilities

Note: SQL Injection Detection
Process called "detect_sql_injection" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect SQL injection vulnerabilities in stack traces
    Let sql_injection_vulns be list containing Note: Check exception message for SQL injection indicators
            Let message_indicators be list containing
            "SQL syntax error", "mysql_query", "ORA-", "sqlite3.OperationalError",
            "PostgreSQL", "SELECT times FROM", "INSERT INTO", "UPDATE", "DELETE FROM",
            "UNION SELECT", "ORDER BY", "GROUP BY", "'; DROP", "--", "/*"
    For each indicator in message_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as indicator:
            Let sql_vuln be create_sql_injection_vulnerability with
            indicator as indicator and
            exception as exception and
            confidence as 0.8
            Add to sql_injection_vulns sql_vuln
    Break Note: Found SQL injection indicator Note: Check stack frames for SQL-related functions
    For each frame in exception.stack_frames:
            Let sql_functions be list containing "execute", "query", "prepare", "exec", "sql"
    For each sql_func in sql_functions:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.function_name and substring as sql_func:
            Let context_vuln be create_sql_context_vulnerability with
            frame as frame and
            exception as exception
    Add to sql_injection_vulns context_vuln Note: Check for dynamic SQL construction patterns
    For each frame in exception.stack_frames:
    For each var_name and var_value in frame.local_variables:
    If var_name contains "sql" or var_name contains "query":
            Let dynamic_sql_vuln be create_dynamic_sql_vulnerability with
            frame as frame and
            variable as var_name and
            exception as exception
            Add to sql_injection_vulns dynamic_sql_vuln Return sql_injection_vulns

Process called "create_sql_injection_vulnerability" that takes indicator as String and exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and confidence as Float returns SecurityVulnerability:
    Note: Create SQL injection vulnerability finding
            Let attack_vectors be list containing
    AttackVector with:
            vector_type as DataExfiltration
            description as "Attacker could extract sensitive data from database"
            prerequisites as list containing "User input reaches SQL query"
            impact_level as High
            exploitability as Moderate
            metadata as dictionary containing "data_access" as true,
    AttackVector with:
            vector_type as DataManipulation
            description as "Attacker could modify or delete database records"
            prerequisites as list containing "Write access to database"
            impact_level as High
            exploitability as Moderate
            metadata as dictionary containing "data_modification" as true Let remediation_steps be list containing
    RemediationStep with:
            step_id as "sql_injection_remediation_001"
            category as InputValidation
            description as "Use parameterized queries or prepared statements instead of dynamic SQL"
            code_example as Some with value as "SELECT times FROM users WHERE id = ? AND name = ?"
            priority as Immediate
            estimated_effort as Hours
            dependencies as list containing
            verification_method as "Code review and security testing"
            metadata as dictionary containing "technique" as "parameterized_queries",
    RemediationStep with:
            step_id as "sql_injection_remediation_002"
            category as InputValidation
            description as "Implement input validation and sanitization"
            code_example as Some with value as "Validate input against whitelist of allowed characters"
            priority as High
            estimated_effort as Days
            dependencies as list containing "sql_injection_remediation_001"
            verification_method as "Penetration testing"
            metadata as dictionary containing "technique" as "input_validation"
    Return SecurityVulnerability with:
            vulnerability_id as "SQL_INJECTION_" generate_vulnerability_id
            vulnerability_type as SQLInjection
            severity_level as High
            title as "SQL Injection Vulnerability Detected"
    description as "SQL injection indicator found: " indicator ". This suggests user input may be directly concatenated into SQL queries."
            affected_components as extract_affected_components with exception as exception
            attack_vectors as attack_vectors
            cve_references as list containing "CWE-89"
            remediation_steps as remediation_steps
            confidence_score as confidence
            risk_score as calculate_risk_score with severity as High and exploitability as Moderate
            metadata as dictionary containing "indicator" as indicator, "detection_method" as "message_analysis"

Note: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Detection
Process called "detect_cross_site_scripting" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect XSS vulnerabilities in web application stack traces
    Let xss_vulns be list containing Note: XSS indicators in error messages
            Let xss_indicators be list containing
    "<script>", "</script>", "javascript:", "onerror=", "onload=", "alert(",
            "document.cookie", "innerHTML", "outerHTML", "eval(", "setTimeout(",
    "href=javascript:", "src=javascript:", "expression("
    For each indicator in xss_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as indicator:
            Let xss_vuln be create_xss_vulnerability with
            indicator as indicator and
            exception as exception and
            xss_type as ReflectedXSS
    Add to xss_vulns xss_vuln Note: Check for web-related stack frames
            Let web_indicators be list containing "render", "template", "html", "response", "output"
    For each frame in exception.stack_frames:
    For each web_indicator in web_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.function_name and substring as web_indicator:
            Let context_xss_vuln be create_xss_context_vulnerability with
            frame as frame and
            exception as exception
            Add to xss_vulns context_xss_vuln Return xss_vulns

Process called "create_xss_vulnerability" that takes indicator as String and exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo and xss_type as XSSType returns SecurityVulnerability:
    Note: Create XSS vulnerability finding
            Let attack_vectors be list containing
    AttackVector with:
            vector_type as DataExfiltration
            description as "Attacker could steal user session cookies and sensitive information"
            prerequisites as list containing "User visits malicious link or page"
            impact_level as Medium
            exploitability as Easy
            metadata as dictionary containing "session_hijacking" as true,
    AttackVector with:
            vector_type as SystemCompromise
            description as "Attacker could perform actions on behalf of the user"
            prerequisites as list containing "Valid user session"
            impact_level as High
            exploitability as Easy
            metadata as dictionary containing "session_riding" as true Let remediation_steps be list containing
    RemediationStep with:
            step_id as "xss_remediation_001"
            category as OutputEncoding
            description as "Implement proper output encoding/escaping for user data"
            code_example as Some with value as "Use HTML entity encoding for user input in HTML context"
            priority as Immediate
            estimated_effort as Hours
            dependencies as list containing
            verification_method as "Manual testing and automated scanning"
            metadata as dictionary containing "technique" as "output_encoding",
    RemediationStep with:
            step_id as "xss_remediation_002"
            category as InputValidation
            description as "Implement Content Security Policy (CSP)"
    code_example as Some with value as "Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'"
            priority as High
            estimated_effort as Days
            dependencies as list containing
            verification_method as "Browser testing"
            metadata as dictionary containing "technique" as "csp"
    Return SecurityVulnerability with:
            vulnerability_id as "XSS_" generate_vulnerability_id
            vulnerability_type as CrossSiteScripting
            severity_level as Medium
            title as "Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Vulnerability Detected"
    description as "XSS indicator found: " indicator ". User input may be rendered without proper encoding."
            affected_components as extract_affected_components with exception as exception
            attack_vectors as attack_vectors
            cve_references as list containing "CWE-79"
            remediation_steps as remediation_steps
            confidence_score as 0.7
            risk_score as calculate_risk_score with severity as Medium and exploitability as Easy
            metadata as dictionary containing "indicator" as indicator, "xss_type" as format_xss_type with xss_type as xss_type

Note: Path Traversal Detection
Process called "detect_path_traversal" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect path traversal vulnerabilities
    Let path_traversal_vulns be list containing Note: Path traversal indicators
            Let path_indicators be list containing
            "../", "..\\", "....//", "....\\\\", "/etc/passwd", "/windows/system32",
    "%2e%2e%2f", "%2e%2e\\", "..%252f", "..%255c", "file://", "..;/"
    For each indicator in path_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as indicator:
            Let path_vuln be create_path_traversal_vulnerability with
            indicator as indicator and
            exception as exception
    Add to path_traversal_vulns path_vuln Note: Check for file operation functions in stack
            Let file_functions be list containing "open", "read", "write", "file", "path", "directory"
    For each frame in exception.stack_frames:
    For each file_func in file_functions:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.function_name and substring as file_func:
            Let file_access_vuln be create_file_access_vulnerability with
            frame as frame and
            exception as exception
            Add to path_traversal_vulns file_access_vuln Return path_traversal_vulns

Process called "create_path_traversal_vulnerability" that takes indicator as String and exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns SecurityVulnerability:
    Note: Create path traversal vulnerability finding
            Let attack_vectors be list containing
    AttackVector with:
            vector_type as InformationGathering
            description as "Attacker could read sensitive system files"
            prerequisites as list containing "File path parameter under user control"
            impact_level as High
            exploitability as Easy
            metadata as dictionary containing "file_disclosure" as true,
    AttackVector with:
            vector_type as SystemCompromise
            description as "Attacker could access configuration files and credentials"
            prerequisites as list containing "Read access to file system"
            impact_level as High
            exploitability as Moderate
            metadata as dictionary containing "credential_access" as true Let remediation_steps be list containing
    RemediationStep with:
            step_id as "path_traversal_remediation_001"
            category as InputValidation
            description as "Validate and sanitize file paths, reject '..' sequences"
            code_example as Some with value as "Resolve canonical path and check if it starts with allowed directory"
            priority as Immediate
            estimated_effort as Hours
            dependencies as list containing
            verification_method as "Path validation testing"
            metadata as dictionary containing "technique" as "path_validation",
    RemediationStep with:
            step_id as "path_traversal_remediation_002"
            category as AccessControl
            description as "Implement file system access controls and chroot jail"
            code_example as None
            priority as High
            estimated_effort as Days
            dependencies as list containing "path_traversal_remediation_001"
            verification_method as "Security architecture review"
            metadata as dictionary containing "technique" as "access_control"
    Return SecurityVulnerability with:
            vulnerability_id as "PATH_TRAVERSAL_" generate_vulnerability_id
            vulnerability_type as PathTraversal
            severity_level as High
            title as "Path Traversal Vulnerability Detected"
    description as "Path traversal indicator found: " indicator ". File paths may not be properly validated."
            affected_components as extract_affected_components with exception as exception
            attack_vectors as attack_vectors
            cve_references as list containing "CWE-22"
            remediation_steps as remediation_steps
            confidence_score as 0.85
            risk_score as calculate_risk_score with severity as High and exploitability as Easy
            metadata as dictionary containing "indicator" as indicator, "detection_method" as "path_analysis"

Note: Authentication and Authorization Detection
Process called "detect_authentication_issues" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect authentication and authorization issues
    Let auth_vulns be list containing Note: Authentication bypass indicators
            Let auth_indicators be list containing
            "authentication failed", "login failed", "unauthorized", "forbidden",
            "access denied", "permission denied", "credential", "password",
            "token expired", "session expired", "invalid token"
    For each indicator in auth_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as indicator:
            Let auth_vuln be create_authentication_vulnerability with
            indicator as indicator and
            exception as exception
    Add to auth_vulns auth_vuln Note: Check for authentication-related functions
            Let auth_functions be list containing "login", "authenticate", "authorize", "verify", "validate"
    For each frame in exception.stack_frames:
    For each auth_func in auth_functions:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.function_name and substring as auth_func:
            Let auth_context_vuln be create_auth_context_vulnerability with
            frame as frame and
            exception as exception
            Add to auth_vulns auth_context_vuln Return auth_vulns

Note: Cryptographic Weakness Detection
Process called "detect_cryptographic_weaknesses" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect cryptographic weaknesses and misconfigurations
    Let crypto_vulns be list containing Note: Weak cryptography indicators
            Let crypto_indicators be list containing
            "MD5", "SHA1", "DES", "RC4", "SSL", "TLS", "certificate", "cipher",
            "weak", "deprecated", "insecure", "key too short", "padding"
    For each indicator in crypto_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as indicator:
            Let crypto_vuln be create_cryptographic_vulnerability with
            indicator as indicator and
            exception as exception
            Add to crypto_vulns crypto_vuln Return crypto_vulns

Note: Information Disclosure Detection
Process called "detect_information_disclosure" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect information disclosure vulnerabilities
    Let info_vulns be list containing Note: Check if stack trace itself reveals sensitive information
            Let sensitive_patterns be list containing
            "password", "secret", "key", "token", "credential", "api_key",
    "/home/", "/usr/", "C:\\", "database", "connection", "config"
    For each pattern in sensitive_patterns:
    For each frame in exception.stack_frames:
            If StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.file_path and substring as pattern or
    StringUtils.string_contains with string as frame.source_line and substring as pattern:
            Let info_vuln be create_information_disclosure_vulnerability with
            pattern as pattern and
            frame as frame and
            exception as exception
    Add to info_vulns info_vuln Note: Check exception message for sensitive data
    For each pattern in sensitive_patterns:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as pattern:
            Let message_info_vuln be create_message_information_disclosure_vulnerability with
            pattern as pattern and
            exception as exception
            Add to info_vulns message_info_vuln Return info_vulns

Note: Input Validation Failure Detection
Process called "detect_input_validation_failures" that takes exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns List[SecurityVulnerability]:
    Note: Detect input validation failures that could lead to vulnerabilities
    Let validation_vulns be list containing Note: Input validation failure indicators
            Let validation_indicators be list containing
            "invalid input", "malformed", "parsing error", "format error",
            "validation failed", "constraint violation", "out of range", "buffer overflow"
    For each indicator in validation_indicators:
    If StringUtils.string_contains with string as exception.exception_message and substring as indicator:
            Let validation_vuln be create_input_validation_vulnerability with
            indicator as indicator and
            exception as exception
            Add to validation_vulns validation_vuln Return validation_vulns

Note: Security Assessment Functions
Process called "calculate_security_score" that takes vulnerabilities as List[SecurityVulnerability] returns Float:
    Note: Calculate overall security score (0-100, higher is better)
    If length of vulnerabilities = 0:
            Return 100.0 Let total_risk be 0.0
    For each vuln in vulnerabilities:
    Set total_risk to total_risk vuln.risk_score Note: Convert risk to security score (inverse relationship)
    Let max_possible_risk be length of vulnerabilities times 10.0 Note: Max risk score per vulnerability
    Let security_score be 100.0 minus ((total_risk / max_possible_risk) times 100.0) Note: Ensure score is within bounds
    If security_score < 0.0:
            Return 0.0
    Otherwise if security_score > 100.0:
            Return 100.0
    Otherwise:
            Return security_score

Process called "assess_security_risk" that takes vulnerabilities as List[SecurityVulnerability] and exception as TracebackCore.ExceptionInfo returns RiskAssessment:
    Note: Assess overall security risk
            Let highest_severity be Low
            Let confidentiality_impact be None
            Let integrity_impact be None
    Let availability_impact be None Note: Determine highest severity and impacts
    For each vuln in vulnerabilities:
    If vuln.severity_level = Critical:
            Set highest_severity to Critical
    Otherwise if vuln.severity_level = High and highest_severity is not equal to Critical:
    Set highest_severity to High Note: Assess impacts based on vulnerability type
    If vuln.vulnerability_type = SQLInjection or vuln.vulnerability_type = PathTraversal:
            Set confidentiality_impact to High
            Set integrity_impact to High
    Otherwise if vuln.vulnerability_type = CrossSiteScripting:
            Set confidentiality_impact to Medium
            Set integrity_impact as Medium
    Otherwise if vuln.vulnerability_type = InformationDisclosure:
            Set confidentiality_impact to High Let overall_risk be determine_overall_risk_level with severity as highest_severity
    Let urgency be determine_mitigation_urgency with risk_level as overall_risk and vulnerability_count as length of vulnerabilities Return RiskAssessment with:
            overall_risk_level as overall_risk
            confidentiality_impact as confidentiality_impact
            integrity_impact as integrity_impact
            availability_impact as availability_impact
            business_risk_factors as identify_business_risk_factors with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities
            technical_risk_factors as identify_technical_risk_factors with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities
            mitigation_urgency as urgency
            metadata as dictionary containing "assessment_time" as TracebackCore.get_current_timestamp, "vulnerability_types" as get_vulnerability_types with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities

Process called "check_compliance_violations" that takes vulnerabilities as List[SecurityVulnerability] returns List[ComplianceViolation]:
    Note: Check for compliance violations based on found vulnerabilities
    Let violations be list containing For each vuln in vulnerabilities:
    Note: Check OWASP Top 10 compliance
    If vuln.vulnerability_type = SQLInjection:
    Let owasp_violation be ComplianceViolation with:
            standard_name as "OWASP Top 10 2021"
            violation_id as "A03:2021"
            requirement_reference as "A03:2021 – Injection"
            description as "SQL injection vulnerability violates OWASP Top 10 injection prevention requirements"
            compliance_severity as MustFix
            remediation_guidance as "Implement parameterized queries and input validation"
            metadata as dictionary containing "owasp_category" as "Injection"
    Add to violations owasp_violation Otherwise if vuln.vulnerability_type = CrossSiteScripting:
    Let owasp_xss_violation be ComplianceViolation with:
            standard_name as "OWASP Top 10 2021"
            violation_id as "A03:2021"
            requirement_reference as "A03:2021 – Injection"
            description as "Cross-site scripting vulnerability violates OWASP injection prevention requirements"
            compliance_severity as MustFix
            remediation_guidance as "Implement output encoding and Content Security Policy"
            metadata as dictionary containing "owasp_category" as "Injection"
    Add to violations owasp_xss_violation Note: Check PCI DSS compliance for payment-related vulnerabilities
    If is_payment_related with vuln as vuln:
    Let pci_violation be ComplianceViolation with:
            standard_name as "PCI DSS"
            violation_id as "PCI-6.5.1"
            requirement_reference as "Requirement 6.5.1"
            description as "Vulnerability affects payment processing and violates PCI DSS security requirements"
            compliance_severity as MustFix
            remediation_guidance as "Implement secure coding practices for payment processing"
            metadata as dictionary containing "pci_requirement" as "6.5.1"
            Add to violations pci_violation Return violations

Process called "generate_security_recommendations" that takes vulnerabilities as List[SecurityVulnerability] returns List[SecurityRecommendation]:
    Note: Generate security recommendations based on vulnerabilities
    Let recommendations be list containing Note: General security recommendations based on vulnerability types found
    Let vuln_types be get_unique_vulnerability_types with vulnerabilities as vulnerabilities For each vuln_type in vuln_types:
    If vuln_type = SQLInjection:
            Let sql_rec be create_sql_security_recommendation
            Add to recommendations sql_rec
    Otherwise if vuln_type = CrossSiteScripting:
            Let xss_rec be create_xss_security_recommendation Add to recommendations xss_rec
    Otherwise if vuln_type = PathTraversal:
            Let path_rec be create_path_security_recommendation
    Add to recommendations path_rec Note: Add general security recommendations
            Let general_rec be create_general_security_recommendation with vulnerability_count as length of vulnerabilities
            Add to recommendations general_rec Return recommendations

